<paragraph blockId="7.[160,1156,1624,1719]" lastBlockId="8.[160,1155,142,515]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="1370" pageId="7" pageNumber="1369">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,307,1624,1650]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1369">Colouration.</emphasis>
Wings bi-banded; light castaneous: mandible, palpi, tegula, wing venation, and tarsi; orange: head, mesosoma; castaneous: scape, pedicel, coxae, trochanters, femora, and tibiae; dark castaneous: flagellum; dark castaneous nearly black: metasoma. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,262,142,168]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="1370">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[160,1155,142,515]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1370">
This new species is superficially similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moczar" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[653,738,178,203]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Incertosulcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="1370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="soikai">
<emphasis box="[653,738,178,203]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="1370">I. soikai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the head and mesosoma orange, the flagellum dark castaneous, the head longer than wide, and the pronotal longitudinal sulcus complete. However, this is the first brachypterous species of this genus. 
<taxonomicName authority="Barbosa &amp; Azevedo, 2020" authorityName="Barbosa &amp; Azevedo" authorityYear="2020" box="[244,491,282,307]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Incertosulcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="1370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pinotage" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[244,491,282,307]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="1370">Incertosulcus pinotage</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[500,592,282,307]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1370" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, thus has some modifications complementary to this wing condition, such as the anteromesoscutum shorter than mesoscutellum, the notaulus wide, the mesoscutellum short, and the posterior projection of metapectalpropodeal very short. Additionally, 
<taxonomicName authority="Barbosa &amp; Azevedo, 2020" authorityName="Barbosa &amp; Azevedo" authorityYear="2020" box="[563,681,386,411]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Incertosulcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="1370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pinotage" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[563,681,386,411]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="1370">I. pinotage</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[690,779,386,411]" pageId="8" pageNumber="1370" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moczar" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[1035,1118,386,411]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Incertosulcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="1370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="soikai">
<emphasis box="[1035,1118,386,411]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="1370">I. soikai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the median clypeal lobe quadrate, the eye small, the ocelli very small, the longitudinal antero-mesoscutal sulcus present, the metapostnotum without longitudinal ridge between metaposnotal median carina and metaposnotal-propodeal suture.
</paragraph>
